JOHANNESBURG – South African sprinter Carina Horn has broken the South African women's 100m record. .@Carinahorn has broken the SA women's 100m record, winning her semifinal in 11.03. Can she go even faster in tomorrow's final? Great performance! #topuptuks Horn clocked 11.03 seconds, winning her semifinal run in the Athletics South Africa Senior Championships in Pretoria on Thursday. RECORD ALERT: @Carinahorn has broken the #RSA women’s 100m record, clocking 11.03 secs to win her semifinal, on Day 1 of the 2018 Athletics South Africa (ASA) Senior Track & Field Championships in Tshwane. #FillUpTuks #SouthAfrica pic.twitter.com/9TGBmYNCVi eNCA